We are growing and need to recruit a new wolf to join the Wolf Pack!

Established in 2007, Silver Wolf Projects(Pty) Ltd is a growing mid-sized
Engineering and Building Consultancy firm that specializes in the insurance
industry offering dynamic, innovative engineering, building consulting and
project management services, using the latest technology to deliver the right
solution quickly.

As a Civil/Structural Engineer with a minimum of two years Australian based
design consultancy experience, you will engage directly with builders,
insurance companies, loss adjusters, and clients to ensure that high quality
forensic civil/structural technical and building reports with cost effective
engineering and remedial solutions are delivered on time.

Depending on your background, duties could include

  * Production of Engineering Reports, Scopes of Works and Design Plans 
  * Structural & Civil Design 
  * Technical Report writing 
  * Use of various engineering software programs 
  * Building and BCA documentation, planning and reporting 
  * Estimating and contract management 
  * AutoCAD/Revit drafting 
  * Insurance inspections on site 

You will have:

  * A minimum of two years solid experience in a design consultancy firm 
  * Thorough knowledge of the BCA and relevant Australian standards 
  * A positive “can do” attitude and willingness to learn 
  * Good technical writing and communication skills 
  * The ability to work as a team player, willing to support colleagues 
  * The willingness to embrace change and new technology 
  * AutoCAD/Revit skills 
  * Microsoft Office suite experience including intermediate Excel skills 

We offer the opportunity to continue your professional development and will
support you in learning all processes, whilst you work as part of a close knit
team in our friendly office. We will support further relevant study and pay
your Engineering Australia fees.

Please apply with a resume and covering letter. If you would like any further
information, please contact Gail Howard on [ 02 8580 7934 ](tel:02 8580 7934)
.

